On 30.9.1896 the part in Merionethshire was transferred to 
    Caernarvonshire, so that thereafter Beddgelert was wholly in 
    Caernarvonshire. See also Table 2, note (c).
Abolished 25.3.1886 and added to the parish of Dolbenmaen.

Abolished 1.4.1897 and incorporated into the parishes of Penrhyndeudraeth 
    and Talsarnau.
Abolished 25.3.1886 and added to the parish of Dolbenmaen.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Dolbenmaen, 
    Ynyscynhaiarn and Criccieth. See also Table 2, note (c).
